[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Q5[bold]) [bold]What role should the [bold]BBC play in developing [bold]technology[bold] and new ways of distributing content?[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]42.
[normal]&#xa0; 
[normal]The BBC’s role is to innovate 
[normal]on behalf of audiences and ensure that the benefits of new 
[normal]digital 
[normal]technologies are available to all. 
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]43.
[normal]&#xa0; 
[normal]Set up by pioneers of the wireless in 1922
[normal],
[normal] the BBC has 
[normal]a strong track record in 
[normal]technology
[normal] innovation
[normal], 
[normal]including 
[normal]FM radio, DAB, colour TV, NICAM sound, Ceefax, and interactive TV and driving international standards and hardware designs for 
[normal]digital terre
[normal]strial television
[normal] (DTT)
[normal]. 
[normal]This has been made possible by 
[normal]a combination of 
[normal]our R&amp;D expertise, long-term perspective and access to stable funding. 
[normal]We can be an early-mover where commercial risks may be too high
[normal] for others
[normal], and can help in coordinating the ind
[normal]ustry to achieve collaborative initiatives and open standards – as, for example, our pan-industry work developing standards with groups such as the Digital Video Broadcasting Project (DVB) and our incubation of YouView (based on open standards and licensed
[normal] to third parties). 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]44.
[normal]&#xa0; 
[normal]Back in 2002, DTT was in crisis. 
[normal]A coalition, led by the BBC, re-built the platform. 
[normal]Today, Freeview is the most popular TV platform in the UK, used in three-quarters of TV households
[normal], providing more choice for viewers, and a 
[normal]platform for dozens of new commercial digital channels.
[normal] The BBC often works through joint ventures and partnerships
[normal] 
[normal]to make synergies across the industry, and in regional hubs to promote economic development across the UK
[normal] 
[normal]. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]45.
[normal]&#xa0; 
[normal]The BBC has a market leadersh
[normal]ip role to play in launching new services based on new technologies.  We can take the lead even where business models are unclear, thus helping commercial players to enter new markets when the opportunities become 
[normal]clearer. 
[normal]BBC Online 
[normal](launched in 1997) 
[normal]was
[normal] a 
[normal]‘pull’
[normal] factor
[normal] for early adopters of the internet
[normal] and 
[normal]BBC 
[normal]iPlayer
[normal] (launched in 2007) 
[normal]stimulated demand for on-demand TV, where the UK 
[normal]now 
[normal]has a leading position.
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]46.
[normal]&#xa0; 
[normal]The 
[normal]final 
[normal]part of the BBC’s role is to ensure t
[normal]hat the
[normal] benefits of digital technologies are available to all not just ‘early adopters’. We 
[normal]use our trusted brand and marketing capabilit
[normal]y
[normal] to 
[normal]inspire confidence, 
[normal]present 
[normal]the benefits of 
[normal]new technologies
[normal],
[normal] 
[normal]and signpost assistance
[normal]. 
[normal]From 2015, we will play a similar role for digital creativity, launching a major project to promote coding and programming, just as we did for basic computing and software in the 1980s through BBC Micro. 
